---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cermat Tutorial"
  description="MVP tutorial app for Czech grade 9 math entrance exam prep"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="pill-row">
      <span class="pill">Exam Tutorial</span>
      <span class="pill">Mistake Review</span>
      <span class="pill">Czech + Ukrainian support</span>
    </div>
    <h1>Step-by-step exam prep, not a textbook and not a quiz bank.</h1>
    <p>
      This MVP follows the real exam order and teaches through tiny decisions. The student sees
      Czech exam text, can reveal Ukrainian help locally, and gets short review tasks based on
      actual mistakes.
    </p>
    <div class="action-row">
      <a class="button" href="/tutorials">Vybrat tutorial</a>
      <a class="button secondary" href="/review">Mistake Review</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Main mode</h2>
      <p>
        Exam Tutorial keeps the real route of tasks 1–16, but the first runnable MVP seed focuses
        on Tutorial A tasks 1–4 with guided steps and feedback.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Language behavior</h2>
      <p>
        Task statements, step prompts, and answer options stay in Czech. Hints, feedback, and
        summaries stay in Ukrainian. Translation is local per segment, never global.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Persistence</h2>
      <p>
        Step attempts, hints, translation reveals, time spent, and weak-skill signals are stored
        in browser progress now and can sync to a Cloudflare Durable Object in deployment.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
